\pard\f0\fs28 Small aquatic plants. Leaves always harbouring the blue-green alga {\i Anabaena}, the upper lobe herbaceous, the lower larger and hyaline. Microsporangia producing several groups of microspores (massulae), often covered with specialized hairs (glochidia); megasporangia producing a single megaspore with 3 floats, which germinates at the water surface to produce a small prothallus.
\par

